args: Malka says that if I want to be a great\nblacksmith, I need to go out and\nexperience lots of new things.
So what should I start with...?
Oh, hey! That looks like Estelle\nand some kids over there.
Today, we will play at the flower fields\nin the nearby forest.
Can I call my animal friends?
The birds would be one thing,\nbut I can't look after a bear.
Hmm, I've never babysat kids before.
...And this is the perfect chance to try!
Heya, Estelle! Need a hand with the kids?
Now be good and play here—\nand don't wander off!
We'll turn you into something pretty!
(Oh man, these two are ADORBS.\nI had no idea looking after kids\nwould actually be fun!)
*sniff* I can't put these together! Waaaah!
Easy, guys! Just gimme the flowers\nand I'll show you how it's done.
See? You just thread the stems together\nlike this, aaaaand...there! Done.
Yaaaay! My big sister helped me!
Ahh... That has SUCH a nice ring to it.
Right then! From this day forward,\nyou're gonna be my little sister!
Now I've got three sisters, which is great.\nNo, wait! Maribelle! I have FOUR sist...
Hee hee! Come back, Mr. Butterfly!
Oh man... Thank goodness Estelle\nwas on top of that.
You mustn't go off alone like that.\nYou might get lost.
Now come back to the field with us.
You don't need to baby me!\nI'm used to the forest!
Your knowledge is not the issue—\nyour naughtiness is.
And naughty children get visited\nby scary ghosts at night!
Why are you shaking so much?\nIs it 'cause you're scared of gh—
O-of course I'm not scared of ghosts!\nThat's crazy. YOU'RE crazy! Don't be crazy!
Oh, well, that's good to hear...\n'Cause there's one behind you.
Er, I think Maribelle was just teasing.
S-s-so there AREN'T ghosts behind me?
I'm sorry. I didn't know they\nscared you that much.
*sniff* Rena used to tell me that ghosts\nwould come get me if I was naughty...
Maybe, but you're a good girl,\nso no ghost will ever come for you.
Okay, I think I feel better—HEY!\nThis is all backwards!
I'M supposed to be the big sister!
Yeah, but if you're this scared of ghosts,\nI think WE'RE actually the big sisters.
But don't worry—it's all fine. There, there.
THIS IS NOT HOW THIS IS\nSUPPOSED TO GO!
Ugh. I know I wanted to experience\nnew things, but not like THIS...
